00:01:50.735 --> 00:01:54.400
Let's add y value of 100.

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:56.855
So we can see what that just did.

00:01:56.855 --> 00:01:59.555
We've translated the reference points,

00:01:59.555 --> 00:02:01.325
which was originally 0,

00:02:01.325 --> 00:02:03.760
0 in the top corner.

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:10.660
Then we've moved the reference point to be 100 across and 100 down on the y axis.

00:02:10.660 --> 00:02:18.510
We can also rotate our triangle or rotate our drawing by using the rotate method.

00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:21.980
By using rotate, the default value,

00:02:21.980 --> 00:02:25.700
which we're at, is in radians rather than degrees.

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:27.860
So to convert to degrees,

00:02:27.860 --> 00:02:36.875
we need to multiply the degrees by maf.pi divided by 180.

00:02:36.875 --> 00:02:39.740
Same value that we had at the start,

00:02:39.740 --> 00:02:43.235
such as 45, will then be in degrees.

00:02:43.235 --> 00:02:47.970
This will rotate the rectangle by 45 degrees.

00:02:47.970 --> 00:02:52.960
We just got to be careful when using translate and rotate both together.

00:02:52.960 --> 00:02:55.420
We need to add translate first.

00:02:55.420 --> 00:02:59.515
Because if we don't, the rotation points is the Canvas origin,

00:02:59.515 --> 00:03:01.715
which is the top left-hand corner.

00:03:01.715 --> 00:03:05.890
So just make sure these two are applied in the correct order.

